<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.53.30-31_0001a" />


<note type="curatorial">419-1</note>

<opener>
<dateline>Nov. 17, '67</dateline>

<salute><hi rend="underline">Dear</hi> Lucile:</salute>
</opener>
<p>This is what I did not say in my dictated letter enclosed herewith: yes, "pallid" <hi rend="underline">is</hi> the word for my reference to our "old friendship". The fact is that I have loved you a long while, and, at the same time,

<pb facs="nei.j4c.53.30-31_0001b"/>
<fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>

as you say, I have <hi rend="underline">liked you too</hi>.</p>

<p>It is in the <hi rend="underline">Pattern of Things</hi> that we should be associated in the work undertaken long ago.</p>
<closer>
<signed>&#8212; John</signed>
</closer>

<fw type="curatorial">30</fw>

</div1>
